trans-unit.source: Represents a Windows status bar control.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en Windows status for kontroll.

trans-unit.source: Although <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripStatusLabel"></xref> replaces and adds functionality to the StatusBar control of previous versions, StatusBar is retained for both backward compatibility and future use if you choose.
trans-unit.target: Selv om <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripStatusLabel"> </xref> erstatter og legger til funksjoner til Vis / Statuslinjekontrollen i tidligere versjoner, Vis/statuslinjen er beholdt for bakoverkompatibilitet og fremtidig bruk hvis du velger.

trans-unit.source: Typically, a StatusBar control consists of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> objects, each of which displays text and/or an icon.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis en Statuslinjekontrollen består av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>objekter, der hver viser tekst og/eller et ikon.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>

trans-unit.source: You can also provide owner-drawn panels to provide custom panels such as a progress bar or a series of images that displays the state of your application.
trans-unit.target: Du kan også angi eieren tegnes paneler Hvis du vil angi egendefinerte paneler for eksempel en pågår linje eller en rekke bilder som viser tilstanden til programmet.

trans-unit.source: A StatusBar control typically displays information about an object being viewed on a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form>, the object's components, or contextual information that relates to that object's operation within your application.
trans-unit.target: En Statuslinjekontrollen vanligvis viser informasjon om et objekt som vises i en <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form>, objektets komponenter eller kontekstavhengig informasjon som er knyttet til dette objektet operasjonen i programmet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form>

trans-unit.source: The StatusBar control provides properties that enable you to customize the appearance of the control.
trans-unit.target: Vis / Statuslinjekontrollen inneholder egenskaper som gjør det mulig å tilpasse utseendet til kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: If the StatusBar is displayed on a form that can be resized, you can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.SizingGrip%2A> property to display a sizing grip in the lower-right corner of the form to indicate to users that the form can be resized.
trans-unit.target: Hvis statuslinjen vises i et skjema som kan endres, kan du bruke den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.SizingGrip%2A>til å vise skalering kontroll nedre høyre hjørne i skjemaet for å angi brukerne at formatet kan endres.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.SizingGrip%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.ShowPanels%2A> property enables you to display panels within your StatusBar or to display only the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A> property of the control.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.ShowPanels%2A>egenskapen kan du vise paneler i din Vis/statuslinjen eller Vis verdien i den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A>-egenskapen for kontrollen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.ShowPanels%2A>

trans-unit.source: The default StatusBar has no panels.
trans-unit.target: Standard Vis/statuslinjen har ingen paneler.

trans-unit.source: To add panels to a StatusBar you can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> class that is accessible through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A> property of the control.
trans-unit.target: Å legge til paneler i en Vis/statuslinjen kan du bruke den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>klasse som er tilgjengelig via den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A>-egenskapen for kontrollen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A>

trans-unit.source: You can also use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> object provided through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A> property to remove panels from the control and access a specific <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> to manipulate the panel.
trans-unit.target: Du kan også bruke den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>gjennom det angitte objektet i <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A>til å fjerne paneler fra kontrollen, og få tilgang til en bestemt <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>til å redigere panelet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>

trans-unit.source: If you want to determine when a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> object within a StatusBar control is clicked, you can create an event handler for the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.PanelClick> event.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil finne ut når en <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>objekt i en Statuslinjekontrollen klikkes, kan du opprette en hendelsesbehandling for den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.PanelClick>hendelsen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.PanelClick> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>

trans-unit.source: To perform owner-draw operations on a panel, you can create an event handler for the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.DrawItem> event.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil utføre eieren-draw-operasjoner i et panel, kan du opprette en hendelsesbehandling for den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.DrawItem>hendelsen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.DrawItem>

trans-unit.source: The event data passed to the event handler provides information on the panel to draw and a <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics> object to use to perform drawing tasks.
trans-unit.target: Hendelsesdata som er sendt til hendelsesbehandlingen gir informasjon om panelet til å tegne og en <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics>objekt som skal brukes til å utføre tegning oppgaver.</xref:System.Drawing.Graphics>

trans-unit.source: Occurs when a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel"></xref> object on a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar"></xref> control is clicked.

trans-unit.source: You can use this event to perform tasks when a panel within a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control is clicked.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke denne hendelsen til å utføre oppgaver når et panel i en <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontrollen klikkes.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: The data provided to the event through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanelClickEventArgs> passed as a parameter to the event handler enables you to determine the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> that was clicked by the user in order to perform tasks on the selected panel.
trans-unit.target: Data som er angitt for hendelsen via den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanelClickEventArgs>sendt som en parameter til hendelsesbehandlingen kan du bestemme den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>som ble klikket av brukeren for å utføre oppgaver i det valgte panelet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanelClickEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: Gets the collection of <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar"></xref> panels contained within the control.
trans-unit.target: Henter samlingen av <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar"> </xref> paneler i kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control can display a number of panels to provide information to the user of your application.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontrollen kan vise flere paneler å gi informasjon til brukeren av programmet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: For example, a panel could display the current time or the progress of a file download.
trans-unit.target: Et panel kan for eksempel vise gjeldende klokkeslett eller fremdriften for filnedlastingen en.

trans-unit.source: Each panel displayed by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control is an instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> class.
trans-unit.target: Hvert panel vises av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontrollen er en forekomst av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>klassen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: The Panels property enables you to obtain a reference to the collection of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> objects that are currently stored in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen paneler gjør det mulig å hente en referanse til samlingen av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>objekter som er lagret i det <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontroll.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>

trans-unit.source: With this reference, you can add panels, remove panels, access a specific panel within the collection, and obtain a count of the panels in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control.
trans-unit.target: Med denne referansen du kan legge til paneler, Fjern paneler, tilgang til et bestemt panel i samlingen, og få et antall paneler i den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontroll.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: For more information on the tasks that can be performed with the panel collection, see the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> class reference topics.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon om oppgavene som kan utføres med panelet-samling, kan du se den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>klasse referanse emner.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> containing the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel"></xref> objects of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>som inneholder den <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel"> </xref> objekter av den <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar"> </xref> kontroll.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a value indicating whether any panels that have been added to the control are displayed.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir en verdi som angir om paneler som er lagt til i kontrollen skal vises.

trans-unit.source: By default, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control displays the value of its <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A> property without any panels.
trans-unit.target: Som standard i <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontrollen viser verdien for den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A>egenskapen uten noen paneler.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: When `ShowPanels` is set to `true`, any <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel> objects specified in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control are displayed.
trans-unit.target: Når `ShowPanels` er satt til `true`, noen <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>objekter som angis i den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontrollen skal vises.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBarPanel>

trans-unit.source: No panels are initially created when you create an instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> class.
trans-unit.target: Ingen paneler opprettes opprinnelig når du oppretter en forekomst av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>klassen.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: You can add panels to a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> control by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> class.
trans-unit.target: Du kan legge til paneler til en <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>kontroll ved hjelp av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A>metoden for <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection>klasse.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.StatusBarPanelCollection.Add%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>

trans-unit.source: This collection class can be accessed through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A> property of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>.
trans-unit.target: Denne Samlingsklasse kan åpnes via <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A>egenskapen for <xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar>.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.StatusBar.Panels%2A>

trans-unit.source: You can use this property to display a sizing grip to provide an indication to the user when a form is resizable.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke denne egenskapen til å vise skalering kontroll for å gi en indikasjon til brukeren når et skjema er størrelsen.

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form.FormBorderStyle%2A> property of your <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form> is set to a border style that is not resizable, such as<xref:System.Windows.Forms.FormBorderStyle> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.FormBorderStyle>, you should set the SizingGrip property to `false` to prevent the user from thinking that the form can be resized.
